Creating a simple web app where a person can prove they are real by solving a simple challenge (like a CAPTCHA-style puzzle) and then share their proof with another person can be done using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. Below is a single HTML file that accomplishes this.

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Prove You're Real</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: center;
            height: 100vh;
            background-color: #f0f0f0;
            margin: 0;
        }
        h1 {
            color: #333;
        }
        #challenge {
            border: 1px solid #ddd;
            padding: 20px;
            background-color: #fff;
            border-radius: 8px;
            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }
        input[type="text"] {
            padding: 10px;
            margin-top: 10px;
            width: 60%;
            border: 1px solid #ddd;
            border-radius: 4px;
        }
        button {
            margin-top: 10px;
            padding: 10px 20px;
            background-color: #28a745;
            color: white;
            border: none;
            border-radius: 4px;
            cursor: pointer;
        }
        button:disabled {
            background-color: #ccc;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <h1>Prove You're Real</h1>
    <div id="challenge">
        <p>Solve this simple challenge:</p>
        <p>What is 3 + 5?</p>
        <input type="text" id="userAnswer" placeholder="Type your answer...">
        <button id="submitAnswer">Submit Answer</button>
        <p id="resultMessage" style="color: red;"></p>

        <a id="shareLink" href="#" style="display: none;">Share this proof</a>
    </div>

    <script>
        const submitButton = document.getElementById('submitAnswer');
        const userAnswer = document.getElementById('userAnswer');
        const resultMessage = document.getElementById('resultMessage');
        const shareLink = document.getElementById('shareLink');

        submitButton.addEventListener('click', () => {
            const answer = userAnswer.value.trim();
            if (answer === '8') {
                resultMessage.textContent = 'Correct! You are real!';
                resultMessage.style.color = 'green';
                shareLink.style.display = 'block';
                // Create a unique proof URL
                const proofUrl = 'https://yourdomain.com/proof?id=' + btoa('yourUniqueIdentifier'); // Replace this with a real unique identifier
                shareLink.href = proofUrl;
                shareLink.textContent = 'Click here to share your proof!';
            } else {
                resultMessage.textContent = 'Incorrect. Please try again.';
                resultMessage.style.color = 'red';
            }
        });
    </script>

</body>
</html>
```

### Explanation:

1. **HTML Structure**: The app presents a simple question (3 + 5). Users must type the correct answer into an input field.

2. **CSS Styling**: Simple styling is added to make the app look clean and centered on the screen.

3. **JavaScript Logic**: 
    - An event listener captures the click on the "Submit Answer" button.
    - It checks if the answer is '8'. If correct, it displays a success message and provides a shareable link.
    - The link is constructed as a placeholder (`yourdomain.com/proof?id=...`). You'd need to replace `'yourUniqueIdentifier'` with whatever unique identification system you have.

### How to Use:
- Copy the code into an `.html` file.
- Open the file in a web browser.
- Solve the challenge and see your proof link to share.

You can customize the challenge, style, and proof mechanism as needed!
